   3.614254891274554*^9},ExpressionUUID->"a2f7501e-b0c1-45d4-bba3-\
9ded4f5e9da8"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Anonymous functions are easily created in ",
 StyleBox["Mathematica",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " using ",
 StyleBox[ButtonBox["Function ",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->"paclet:ref/Function"],
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "and are very convenient when working with functions such as ",
 StyleBox[ButtonBox["Map",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->"paclet:ref/Map"],
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ". Two things are needed in defining an anonymous function:"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.61425350360015*^9, 3.614253627441738*^9}, {
   3.614253734862137*^9, 3.6142538265745487`*^9}, 3.614950128926064*^9, {
   3.6157351387767973`*^9, 
   3.615735170854438*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"7a3406d4-7bf7-45a4-99db-\
89071d680b06"],

Cell["an ordered list giving the arguments used", "ItemNumbered",
 CellMargins->{{165.24, 30.72}, {10., 10.}},
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.614253861576753*^9, 3.614253879337981*^9}, 
   3.614950130787393*^9, 
   3.615735189686512*^9},ExpressionUUID->"859762bb-fab2-48e6-9d72-\
a7decd98ddd1"],

Cell["\<\
a rule for combining the arguments to give the value returned by the function\
\
\>", "ItemNumbered",
 CellMargins->{{165.24, 30.72}, {10., 10.}},
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.614253883585857*^9, 3.614253915196048*^9}, 
   3.614950133283311*^9, 
   3.615735191099925*^9},ExpressionUUID->"0b0f66a2-d601-4937-b777-\
9d8b9e978d94"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox[ButtonBox["Slot",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->"paclet:ref/Slot"],
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " (#n) can be used to identify the arguments, in which case the ordered list \
of arguments need not be explicitly stated. Names can be assigned to \
anonymous functions, but naming them is not required."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.614253949086368*^9, 3.614253984272552*^9}, {
   3.614254015798977*^9, 3.614254181637455*^9}, 3.614950156954457*^9, {
